---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';

const publishDate = new Date("2025-03-28");
const formattedDate = publishDate.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { 
  year: 'numeric', 
  month: 'long', 
  day: 'numeric' 
});
---

<Layout 
  title="The Rise and Fall of the Cassette Tape"
  description="How this simple magnetic storage device revolutionized portable music and created a mixtape culture that defined a generation, before being replaced by digital formats."
>
  <Hero 
    title="The Rise and Fall of the Cassette Tape"
    subtitle={`Published on ${formattedDate} by Sophia Williams`}
    image="/image7.jpg"
    height="medium"
  />
  
  <article class="py-16 bg-white dark:bg-dark-900">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert lg:prose-lg mx-auto">
          <p class="lead">
            The compact cassette tape, introduced by Philips in 1963, revolutionized how we consumed and shared music, creating a cultural phenomenon that would last for decades.
          </p>

          <h2>The Birth of Portable Music</h2>
          <p>
            Before the cassette tape, music was primarily enjoyed through vinyl records or radio – neither of which offered true portability. The cassette changed everything by making music personal and portable.
          </p>

          <figure class="my-8">
            <img 
              src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/775414/pexels-photo-775414.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
              alt="Vintage cassette player" 
              class="rounded-lg shadow-lg"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-dark-500 dark:text-dark-400 mt-2">
              The iconic Walkman made cassettes truly portable
            </figcaption>
          </figure>

          <h2>Mixtape Culture</h2>
          <p>
            Perhaps the cassette's most significant cultural impact was the mixtape – a carefully curated collection of songs recorded onto a single tape. Mixtapes became a form of personal expression and a way to share music with friends and loved ones.
          </p>

          <h2>Technical Innovation</h2>
          <p>
            The cassette's success wasn't just about convenience. Technical innovations like Dolby noise reduction and chrome and metal tapes significantly improved sound quality, making cassettes a viable alternative to vinyl records.
          </p>

          <blockquote>
            "The cassette tape didn't just change how we listened to music – it changed how we shared our musical identity with others."
          </blockquote>

          <h2>The Digital Revolution</h2>
          <p>
            The introduction of the compact disc in the 1980s began the cassette's slow decline. By the late 1990s, with the rise of MP3 players and digital music, the cassette's era was coming to an end.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8 items-center my-12 p-6 bg-dark-50 dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2">Explore Our Audio Collection</h3>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Visit our extensive collection of vintage audio equipment and learn about the evolution of music playback technology.
              </p>
              <a 
                href="/exhibitions/audio-evolution" 
                class="inline-flex items-center text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
              >
                View the exhibition
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="1.5" stroke="currentColor" class="w-4 h-4 ml-1">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13.5 4.5 21 12m0 0-7.5 7.5M21 12H3" />
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
            <img 
              src="/image10.jpg" 
              alt="Collection of cassette tapes" 
              class="w-full md:w-1/3 rounded-lg shadow-md"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Author Bio -->
        <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-dark-200 dark:border-dark-700">
          <div class="flex items-center">
            <img 
              src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3769021/pexels-photo-3769021.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
              alt="Sophia Williams" 
              class="w-16 h-16 rounded-full object-cover mr-4"
            />
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-lg text-dark-900 dark:text-white">Sophia Williams</h3>
              <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300">
                Audio Technology Historian
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Share and Navigation -->
        <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap justify-between items-center pt-8 border-t border-dark-200 dark:border-dark-700">
          <div class="flex space-x-4">
            <button class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 hover:text-primary-600 dark:hover:text-primary-400">
              Share on Twitter
            </button>
            <button class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 hover:text-primary-600 dark:hover:text-primary-400">
              Share on Facebook
            </button>
          </div>
          <a 
            href="/blog" 
            class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
          >
            Back to Blog
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- Related Articles -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-dark-50 dark:bg-dark-800/50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl text-dark-900 dark:text-white text-center mb-12">
        Related Articles
      </h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/775414/pexels-photo-775414.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
            alt="Vintage audio equipment" 
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-dark-900 dark:text-white">
              The Vinyl Revival
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 mb-4">
              Why vinyl records are making a comeback in the digital age.
            </p>
            <a 
              href="/blog/vinyl-revival" 
              class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
            >
              Read more
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/812968/pexels-photo-812968.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
            alt="CD collection" 
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-dark-900 dark:text-white">
              The CD Revolution
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 mb-4">
              How compact discs changed the music industry forever.
            </p>
            <a 
              href="/blog/cd-revolution" 
              class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
            >
              Read more
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/3951050/pexels-photo-3951050.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1260&h=750&dpr=2" 
            alt="iPod Classic" 
            class="w-full h-48 object-cover"
          />
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-2 text-dark-900 dark:text-white">
              The iPod Generation
            </h3>
            <p class="text-dark-600 dark:text-dark-300 mb-4">
              How Apple's iconic device transformed music consumption.
            </p>
            <a 
              href="/blog/ipod-generation" 
              class="text-primary-600 dark:text-primary-400 hover:underline"
            >
              Read more
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
  
  .prose img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }
  
  .prose h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.875rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: inherit;
  }
  
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }
  
  .prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: italic;
    border-left: 4px solid theme('colors.primary.600');
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  
  .dark .prose blockquote {
    border-left-color: theme('colors.primary.400');
  }
</style>